<div><h3>EDUC 152 - Complexities of Urban Schooling </h3>  <hr>This course will examine the history, goals, purpose, and challenges of schooling in the US, and in particular, schooling in urban communities. We&#8217;ll explore movements of educational theory and policy, and how they&#8217;ve impacted outcomes for students of different race and class backgrounds, and we&#8217;ll examine the biggest challenges and policy issues facing urban schools in the US today. For undergraduate students interested in educational studies.Â  The course is also a prerequisite for the Education minor and for the Master of Arts in Teaching graduate program.<br><br><strong>Course Designation/Attribute:</strong> DI<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Offered every year<br><br></div>		</td>
